1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,725
And that real run delivered.

2
00:00:01,675 --> 00:00:07,258
We gave Immortals a genuine build — a weekly research digest: a Cloudflare backend plus a Chrome extension, end to end.

3
00:00:07,258 --> 00:00:09,958
Four steps, three specialists, real agents.

4
00:00:09,958 --> 00:00:12,675
It passed all eight of our pre-registered success criteria.

5
00:00:12,675 --> 00:00:16,175
The code it shipped: seventy-eight of seventy-eight tests passing, type-clean.

6
00:00:16,175 --> 00:00:17,966
But here is the moment that matters.

7
00:00:17,966 --> 00:00:25,033
The critic agent — on its own — caught a critical flaw the first plan missed: summarizing one item at a time would blow a hard platform limit and abort the whole digest.

8
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:26,783
The coder fixed it with batching.

9
00:00:26,783 --> 00:00:29,400
The team produced better architecture than the plan it was handed.

10
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:33,875
Honest caveat: the agents build and test headlessly — the final deploy is still a human click.

11
00:00:33,875 --> 00:00:35,866
But that is not one yes-man chatbot.

12
00:00:35,866 --> 00:00:37,783
That is a real, critical team.

